      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Timorith wrote:</div><div class="orig"> <br />As long as archers have an ACC and ATK penalty when attacking targets in melee range, they are simply not able to stand right on a mob.  </div></div> <br /><b>Which is why most conjurers I know don't like adding Archers right now. </b>  <br /> <br />It's better SP wise to pick a Marauder or even another Gladiator for a healer than pick an Archer. With those two classes, it's pretty much a given that they'll even accidentally get hit by some stray AoE and increase your AoE Healing SP.  Archers simply stand too far back to get hit to be worth the add to the party for most healers. <br /> <br /> <br />They also have a side detrimental effect of not being able to control their DPS at times. When an Archer 'steps on the gas', that mob will take some serious damage. Adding two archers makes the mobs too fast, lowering everyone's chance to get good SP, most especially healers. <br /> <br /></div>
